WEBVTT

00:04:56.314 --> 00:05:00.567
The assumption's
that economic agents are rational.

00:05:01.352 --> 00:05:03.956
They're also supposed to be selfish

00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:06.672
and they're also supposed
to know what they want,

00:05:06.696 --> 00:05:11.310
and of course, as a psychologist --
this sounds wrong.

00:05:11.713 --> 00:05:14.093
And of course, economists
know that it's wrong,

00:05:14.117 --> 00:05:16.212
it's just very useful to their theorizing.

00:05:16.236 --> 00:05:18.054
CA: And so was it in the '70s

00:05:18.078 --> 00:05:21.689
that you formed this extraordinary
partnership with Amos Tversky

00:05:21.713 --> 00:05:24.788
and started to question
some of these ideas?

00:05:24.812 --> 00:05:27.509
Tell us about how that happened.

00:05:27.533 --> 00:05:31.827
DK: Our partnership and our friendship
actually started in 1969.